{"amendments":[{"body":"`plan_hash` auto-population still does not repair the legacy rows that motivated Issue 3. New rows get the snapshot hash at `src/adapters/fs.rs:2945-2957`, but once a running/terminal row already exists with `plan_hash: null`, both the replay path in `src/adapters/fs.rs:2909-2923` and the finalize path in `src/adapters/fs.rs:3228-3250` explicitly skip snapshot-based backfill. That means a task-run row written by the old code without `plan_hash` will stay null forever even when the milestone snapshot already has the canonical plan hash, so lineage for pre-upgrade attempts is still incomplete. The new regressions at `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:5122-5308` lock in that lossiness instead of fixing it.","rationale":"This leaves exactly the historical task-run records called out in the prompt without recoverable plan lineage, so debugging/auditing still cannot tell which persisted plan executed those attempts after the upgrade."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone-lineage changes in `src/adapters/fs.rs` and `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs` and ran `cargo test milestone_record`. One correctness gap remains: existing task-run rows with missing `plan_hash` are still never repaired from the snapshot."}